\f0\fs24 \cf0 \{\
  "title": "Should Cardano establish a Sovereign Wealth Fund?",\
  \
  "abstract": "This Info Action proposes that the Cardano community explore the creation of a Sovereign Wealth Fund, seeded from the on-chain treasury, to provide counter-cyclical funding for ecosystem development, infrastructure maintenance, and strategic investment across market cycles.",\
  \
  "motivation": "The Cardano treasury currently receives a portion of transaction fees and monetary expansion each epoch. These funds are available for community-approved withdrawals through the governance process. However, the treasury's real-world purchasing power fluctuates dramatically with the market price of ada. During bull markets, the treasury is flush\'97denominated in ada, its value can reach billions of dollars. During prolonged bear markets, its purchasing power contracts precisely when funding for development and ecosystem maintenance is most critical. The treasury carries a structural vulnerability. Development teams that receive treasury funding during a bull market may find their grants worth a fraction of their original value by the time the work is delivered. Critical infrastructure projects may be deferred because the treasury's purchasing power has fallen below the level needed to fund them. The ecosystem becomes pro-cyclical\'97spending in bull markets and retrenching in bears \'97 the opposite of prudent management.\
  \
    A sovereign wealth fund would address this vulnerability. By allocating a fixed percentage of treasury inflows, say 10%, into a diversified, transparently managed reserve, the ecosystem can build a financial buffer. This reserve would be deployed counter-cyclically: drawn down during downturns, replenished during growth. The model draws inspiration from national sovereign wealth funds like Norway's Government Pension Fund Global, adapted for the unique context of a decentralised protocol.",\
  \
  "rationale": "Implementation would proceed through a series of subsequent governance actions. First, an appropriate legal structure must be established for the fund \'97 a vehicle capable of holding assets, executing investment decisions, and operating within relevant regulatory frameworks. This legal structure would be created and approved as part of the treasury withdrawal action that seeds the fund, not as a separate governance step. Second, the treasury withdrawal itself, transferring the initial seed capital. Third, a transparent, on-chain management framework, ideally through Cardano smart contracts and multi-sig arrangements that prevent unilateral action by any single party. Fourth, regular reporting and audit mechanisms to ensure accountability"\
\}\
\
}